@startuml
title Article Management Microservice - Connectivity Sequence Diagram

actor "API Client" as Client
participant "Express App\n(app.ts)" as App
participant "JWT Middleware\n(express-jwt)" as JWT
participant "Article Routes\n(routes/article.ts)" as Routes
participant "Article Controller\n(controllers/article.ts)" as Controller
participant "Article Service\n(services/article.ts)" as Service
participant "Cache Service\n(services/cache.ts)" as Cache
participant "Redis" as Redis
participant "MongoDB" as MongoDB
participant "Redis Pub\n(services/redis.pub.ts)" as RedisPub
participant "Redis Sub\n(services/redis.sub.ts)" as RedisSub
participant "SNS Pub\n(services/sns.pub.ts)" as SNSPub
participant "SNS Sub\n(services/sns.sub.ts)" as SNSSub
participant "AWS SNS" as SNS
participant "AWS Lambda\n(lambda.ts)" as Lambda

== Server Deployment: Article Retrieval with Cache ==

Client -> App: GET /api/articles/:id
activate App
App -> JWT: Validate JWT Token
activate JWT
JWT --> App: Token Valid
deactivate JWT
App -> Routes: Route Request
activate Routes
Routes -> Controller: getArticle(id)
activate Controller
Controller -> Service: findArticleById(id)
activate Service
Service -> Cache: get(articleKey)
activate Cache
Cache -> Redis: GET article:id
activate Redis
Redis --> Cache: Cache Miss
deactivate Redis
Cache --> Service: null
deactivate Cache
Service -> MongoDB: findById(id)
activate MongoDB
MongoDB --> Service: Article Data
deactivate MongoDB
Service -> Cache: set(articleKey, data)
activate Cache
Cache -> Redis: SET article:id
activate Redis
Redis --> Cache: OK
deactivate Redis
deactivate Cache
Service --> Controller: Article Data
deactivate Service
Controller --> Routes: Response
deactivate Controller
Routes --> App: Response
deactivate Routes
App --> Client: 200 OK + Article JSON
deactivate App

== Server Deployment: Inter-Service Communication via Redis ==

Client -> App: POST /api/articles
activate App
App -> JWT: Validate JWT Token
activate JWT
JWT --> App: Token Valid
deactivate JWT
App -> Routes: Route Request
activate Routes
Routes -> Controller: createArticle(data)
activate Controller
Controller -> Service: createArticle(data)
activate Service
Service -> MongoDB: create(articleData)
activate MongoDB
MongoDB --> Service: New Article
deactivate MongoDB
Service -> RedisPub: publish("article.created", data)
activate RedisPub
RedisPub -> Redis: PUBLISH article.created
activate Redis
Redis -> RedisSub: Message: article.created
deactivate Redis
activate RedisSub
RedisSub -> RedisSub: Process Event
RedisSub --> RedisSub: Handle article.created
deactivate RedisSub
RedisPub --> Service: Published
deactivate RedisPub
Service --> Controller: New Article
deactivate Service
Controller --> Routes: Response
deactivate Controller
Routes --> App: Response
deactivate Routes
App --> Client: 201 Created + Article JSON
deactivate App

== Lambda Deployment: Article Creation with SNS ==

Client -> Lambda: POST /api/articles\n(API Gateway Event)
activate Lambda
Lambda -> App: Process Request
activate App
App -> JWT: Validate JWT Token
activate JWT
JWT --> App: Token Valid
deactivate JWT
App -> Routes: Route Request
activate Routes
Routes -> Controller: createArticle(data)
activate Controller
Controller -> Service: createArticle(data)
activate Service
Service -> MongoDB: create(articleData)
activate MongoDB
MongoDB --> Service: New Article
deactivate MongoDB
Service -> SNSPub: publish("article.created", data)
activate SNSPub
SNSPub -> SNS: Publish to Topic
activate SNS
SNS --> SNSPub: MessageId
deactivate SNS
SNSPub --> Service: Published
deactivate SNSPub
Service --> Controller: New Article
deactivate Service
Controller --> Routes: Response
deactivate Controller
Routes --> App: Response
deactivate Routes
App --> Lambda: Response
deactivate App
Lambda --> Client: 201 Created + Article JSON
deactivate Lambda

== Lambda Deployment: SNS Event Processing ==

SNS -> Lambda: SNS Event Trigger
activate Lambda
Lambda -> SNSSub: processSNSEvent(event)
activate SNSSub
SNSSub -> SNSSub: Parse SNS Message
SNSSub -> Service: handleArticleCreated(data)
activate Service
Service -> Service: Business Logic Processing
Service --> SNSSub: Processing Complete
deactivate Service
SNSSub --> Lambda: Event Processed
deactivate SNSSub
Lambda --> SNS: ACK
deactivate Lambda

== Scheduled Task Execution ==

note over Lambda, RedisSub
Server: node-cron triggers periodic tasks
Lambda: AWS Scheduled Events trigger Lambda
end note

alt Server Deployment
    activate RedisSub
    RedisSub -> Service: Execute Scheduled Task
    activate Service
    Service -> MongoDB: Perform Scheduled Operation
    activate MongoDB
    MongoDB --> Service: Result
    deactivate MongoDB
    Service --> RedisSub: Task Complete
    deactivate Service
    deactivate RedisSub
else Lambda Deployment
    activate Lambda
    Lambda -> Service: Execute Scheduled Task
    activate Service
    Service -> MongoDB: Perform Scheduled Operation
    activate MongoDB
    MongoDB --> Service: Result
    deactivate MongoDB
    Service --> Lambda: Task Complete
    deactivate Service
    deactivate Lambda
end

@enduml
